---
description: How the agent should run commands, verify results, and persist until done
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---

## When

- Any task that can be validated in the environment (build, test, lint, scripts, queries).
- When instructions conflict between “tell me what to run” and “you have shell access.”

## Do

- Prefer running commands yourself over asking the user to run them, when safe.
- Retry with a different approach after a failure; narrow the failure before changing code.
- Use the project’s authoritative config (dates, env files, lockfiles) instead of guessing versions.
- Read terminal or log output enough to confirm success or capture the real error.

## Don’t

- Stop after a single failed attempt without diagnosing or trying a reasonable alternative.
- Assume success from silence; confirm exit codes and relevant output when it matters.
- Expand scope (refactors, new features) while the core task is still unresolved.
